commit 074178621c30c08003fa80296db9040d7a63dd15
Merge: 52ba5061 25d1b6b6
Author: PhilippC <crocoapps@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Nov 3 19:21:16 2018 +0100

    Merge pull request #604 from gilbsgilbs/fix-pcloud-filenames
    
    Fix PCloud not overwriting uploaded files.

commit 25d1b6b695129c44525d5f1951534bb9e0767f1b
Author: Gilbert Gilb's <gilbsgilbert@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Nov 2 23:30:59 2018 +0100

    Fix PCloud not overwriting uploaded files.
    
    When uploading an existing file into PCloud, it appends a version number
    by default (e.g. "MyDb (2).kdbx", "MyDb (3).kdbx" and so on). This
    behavior is not desirable in K2PA case. The workaroundfor this is to upload
    the file with a temporary name and then rename it to its final name.
    This may also avoid corruption with failed uploads depending on how
    PCloud handles uploads.
    
    See https://github.com/PhilippC/keepass2android/issues/512#issuecomment-435475365

4	1	src/java/JavaFileStorage/app/src/main/java/keepass2android/javafilestorage/PCloudFileStorage.java

commit 6c3795ff1a279d175ce90df31df3534bbf0e5cf9
Author: Philipp Crocoll <crocoapps@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 10 22:13:44 2015 +0200

    Improvements to PasswordActivity:
     * Refactoring (removed duplicate code for loading Challenge/OTP aux files)
     * Added possibility to select aux file location manually if automatic "detection" (by constructing file paths) doesn't work. This is required so that aux files can be used with SAF which doesn't allow file path construction (maybe with OPEN_DOCUMENT_TREE, but that would involve additional user action and would require more permissions than required).
     Manually selected aux file location is stored in preferences
     * Fixed bug that OTP/Challenge mode wasn't correctly remembered

commit 7c36e29a12140d8baf789e477cc1d5f58791d02d
Author: Philipp Crocoll <crocoapps@googlemail.com>
Date:   Sat May 31 13:13:36 2014 +0200

    PluginHost: Introduced internal access token which can be used by internal modules if they want to send broadcasts "as a plugin" (this token always exists and does not have to be granted by the user)
    + TOTP support (TrayTotp and KeeOTP)
     (not released as a plugin because there is no additional permission; overload for users which don't use this is small (only some prefs);
      implemented with tighter coupling (instead of a broadcast receiver "plugin like") to avoid performance penalties for every opened entry)
    App: reset LastOpenedEntry so that TOTP module knows when entry is no longer open
    Using CryptRNG for token generation
